meaningMnemonic: To <kanji>take</kanji> something and then <kanji>remove</kanji> it, is when you reach in and grab something and choose it and pull it out. This is <vocabulary>to pick out</vocabulary> or <vocabulary>to take out</vocabulary>.
readingMnemonic: The readings come from the individual words 取る and 出す. Put them together and you should be able to read this word too.
